This paper deals with the theoretical understanding of multitask deep neural networks and their relationship with multitask Gaussian processes. The paper discusses the sharing of information among different tasks in MTDNN and establishes a formal connection between MTDNN and multitask GP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
